narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Immersion, full immersion. I was a little shocked, but not surprised by this; it was a real wakeup call to only hear French. I would recommend taking French at Yale to anyone who is interested because I love the language and the method is so effective.
Great, engaging way to further your French-speaking skills.
I would recommend this class because you learn a lot of French. However, it is also disorganized, which can be very frustrating.
It's a lot of work, if you don't keep up with the workbook exercises you'll be lost because that's where you learn most of the grammar.
